{
  "stem": "4113.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I stopped my cousin from jumping out, or he would be killed as well, and didn't make sense.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Soon, as the dead were collected and taken away we were-- a few airmen came from the airbase with an officer.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were marched to the airbase, to the barracks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "While this was going on in the ghetto-- you know, the collection of the people, the selection-- another group of Gestapo went to the airbase-- there were over 300 Jews working there, with their families at the airbase-- and cleaned it out there.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Took all their wives.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They took their wives, their children away, and many of the older ones and left only about 100, 105 people out of the 300.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they attached those people to the transport that went to the bigger ghetto-- I told you-- in Reichshof, that my little brother, and my cousin, and his boy Michael went to.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were marched over there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was snowing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a Friday morning, the 4th of December.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was snowing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And while we were marching there, a few Jews that were hidden-- you know, on the road somewheres-- they saw us march to the airbase.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They jumped out and attached themselves.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were afraid that we get to the airbase, and they will count us and there's going to be more, you know, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But the-- the airmen didn't give a damn.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I mean, they couldn't care less.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Their job was to bring us to the airbase.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So there we were set up in the barracks there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have to tell you an incident when I got there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a Jewish fellow used to be a neighbor of ours.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was a Hasid.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know what a Hasid is?",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
